{"parentUuid":"0ef5166a-a510-492a-a96b-d4c6538f8479","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01RYNi2RzvBYfaAT5RECnz9A","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFair points. Let me reconsider each:\n\n- **Conversation logs (`.jsonl`)** — They can get large (tens/hundreds of MB over time), which bloats your git repo. But if you want conversation continuity across machines, they're worth syncing.\n- **Plugins** — The `plugins/marketplaces/` folders contain cloned git repos (`.git` dirs inside). Git doesn't handle nested `.git` well — it'll either ignore the inner repo's contents or create submodule confusion. You'd need to either strip the inner `.git` dirs or use submodules.\n- **Session/task/cache data** — No real reason to exclude if you want full continuity. They're small.\n\nSo the only genuinely problematic one is **plugins** due to nested `.git` repos. Here's the updated `.gitignore`:\n\n```gitignore\n# Credentials (NEVER sync)\n.credentials.json\nmcp-needs-auth-cache.json\n\n# Nested git repos inside plugins — strip .git dirs or exclude\nplugins/marketplaces/**/.git/\n\n# Lock files\n**/.lock\n**/.highwatermark\n```\n\nThat's it. Everything else syncs: conversations, sessions, tasks, cache, plans, memories, settings, plugins (minus their inner `.git` dirs).\n\nOne heads-up: your conversation logs will grow over time. You may want to periodically run `git gc` or consider git-lfs for the `.jsonl` files if the repo gets unwieldy."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":338,"cache_read_input_tokens":48069,"output_tokens":345,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":338,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":3,"output_tokens":345,"cache_read_input_tokens":48069,"cache_creation_input_toke